		<h2>Management ≠ Leadership</h2>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-3 col-md-offset-3">
				<p class="align-right">Management is just plain old authority over a group, guiding people through tasks they do all the time.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="col-md-3">
				<p class="align-left"> Leadership is helping people see problems in new ways and encouraging them to find creative solutions</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<h2>That means you have to influence a group.</h2>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-3 col-md-offset-3">
				<p><span class="label">Be a Role Model</span><br>‘do as I say, not what I do’ sucks</p>
			</div>
			<div class="col-md-3">
				<p><span class="label">BE CLEAR</span><br>people should know why they’re doing what they’re doing</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-3 col-md-offset-3">
				<p><span class="label">Teach</span><br>it’s your job to help people gain new skills</p>
			</div>
			<div class="col-md-3">
				<p><span class="label">MAINTAIN STRUCTURE</span><br>set expectations from the start, then stick to them</p>
			</div>
		</div>
